1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,573
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,573 --> 00:00:03,004
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,627 --> 00:00:06,293
The Philosophy Department
is shutting down,

4
00:00:06,293 --> 00:00:08,442
so next month, he'll be unemployed.

5
00:00:09,827 --> 00:00:11,260
- Unemployed?
- No.

6
00:00:11,260 --> 00:00:12,560
That's not it, Mom.

7
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,249
It's true. You won't even have lectures
starting next month.

8
00:00:15,527 --> 00:00:17,084
What does "unemployed" mean, Dad?

9
00:00:17,460 --> 00:00:19,085
I'll explain later.

10
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:21,693
Father already knows,

11
00:00:21,927 --> 00:00:25,058
but it seems you don't,
so I'm telling you.

12
00:00:28,127 --> 00:00:30,827
You already knew?

13
00:00:31,127 --> 00:00:33,827
When you came because you were worried...

14
00:00:33,827 --> 00:00:36,827
about me staying out overnight,
I told Dad.

15
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:40,405
Eun Hyeong had applied
to several other schools...

16
00:00:40,405 --> 00:00:41,641
- and...
- Yes.

17
00:00:42,060 --> 00:00:44,193
I was planning to tell you everything
once the results came out.

18
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,546
You have such high expectations of me,

19
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:48,916
so I couldn't suddenly disappoint you.

20
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:50,627
What's wrong with all of you?

21
00:00:50,627 --> 00:00:53,253
Do you think
I'm that unreasonable and thoughtless?

22
00:00:55,427 --> 00:00:58,574
When do the results come out?

23
00:00:58,727 --> 00:01:00,360
I'm not sure of the exact date.

24
00:01:01,727 --> 00:01:02,963
I'm really sorry, Mom.

25
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,864
Why are you apologizing?

26
00:01:05,393 --> 00:01:07,133
It's not your fault
the department shut down.

27
00:01:07,987 --> 00:01:09,637
I believe in you.

28
00:01:10,207 --> 00:01:13,107
Don't worry. Good news will come soon.

29
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,360
You can all go now.

30
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:20,347
I packed some food in the living room,
so take it.

31
00:01:24,184 --> 00:01:25,184
Don't follow me.

32
00:01:26,627 --> 00:01:28,321
Okay...

33
00:01:31,693 --> 00:01:33,193
You should go and put Bit Na to bed.

34
00:01:33,193 --> 00:01:34,294
Come on, get up.

35
00:01:34,893 --> 00:01:36,603
Please take care of Mom.

36
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:38,227
I'm sorry, Father.

37
00:01:38,227 --> 00:01:40,767
No, it's fine.
She would've found out anyway.

38
00:01:41,893 --> 00:01:43,093
I should've thought it through more.

39
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:47,073
Grandpa, Aunties, bye-bye.

40
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:50,210
Bye-bye, Bit Na.

41
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:51,665
Bye, Eun Hyeong.

42
00:01:52,427 --> 00:01:53,547
Bye, Ji Seon.

43
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:55,749
All right, off you go.

44
00:02:12,693 --> 00:02:13,693
Hello.

45
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:14,901
Hi.

46
00:02:15,693 --> 00:02:19,260
It's been so hard to see you lately,
Ji Seon.

47
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:20,907
Come visit more often.

48
00:02:21,693 --> 00:02:23,560
Grandma, you say the funniest things.

49
00:02:24,093 --> 00:02:25,176
Hello.

50
00:02:25,527 --> 00:02:26,593
Hello.

51
00:02:26,993 --> 00:02:28,860
Bit Na, did you enjoy the party?

52
00:02:28,860 --> 00:02:30,951
No. We didn't have a party.

53
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:33,186
What?
I thought there was a family party today.

54
00:02:33,793 --> 00:02:34,921
Let's go, Bit Na.

55
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:37,660
We'll see you next time.

56
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:38,952
Yes, bye.

57
00:02:41,093 --> 00:02:42,399
I wonder what happened.

58
00:02:42,399 --> 00:02:45,332
The mood feels off.

59
00:02:45,693 --> 00:02:46,693
Right.

60
00:02:47,027 --> 00:02:49,027
You told me before...

61
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,204
not to disappoint Mom.

62
00:02:52,127 --> 00:02:53,774
Now I finally understand.

63
00:02:54,206 --> 00:02:55,742
So do a good job.

64
00:02:55,927 --> 00:02:58,545
You're Mom's last hope now.

65
00:02:59,307 --> 00:03:00,381
Who do you think you're talking to?

66
00:03:00,693 --> 00:03:03,917
For me, it'll be
after I've already prepared everything...

67
00:03:04,819 --> 00:03:05,819
Prepared what?

68
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,060
What?

69
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,256
For the exam, obviously.

70
00:03:11,827 --> 00:03:14,528
Mom must be really upset. This is bad.

71
00:03:14,528 --> 00:03:15,805
If you're that worried,

72
00:03:15,805 --> 00:03:18,866
just settle down at Kangsu Construction.

73
00:03:27,927 --> 00:03:29,142
Why are you out here?

74
00:03:30,227 --> 00:03:31,227
I'll go in soon.

75
00:03:32,593 --> 00:03:35,893
What if Mom finds out
about your situation too, Dad?

76
00:03:36,727 --> 00:03:38,518
Before it's too late, we should...

77
00:03:38,793 --> 00:03:40,493
I have an interview tomorrow.

78
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:42,893
Once it's decided, I'll tell her then.

79
00:03:43,427 --> 00:03:45,393
I really hope it works out.

80
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,093
- Let's go inside.
- Okay.

81
00:04:00,027 --> 00:04:01,027
Are you asleep?

82
00:04:05,026 --> 00:04:06,960
Eun Hyeong must feel a lot of pressure.

83
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,682
Don't be too upset.

84
00:04:11,593 --> 00:04:14,354
Are you hiding anything else from me...

85
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:15,765
besides the Eun Ae and Eun Hyeong issues?

86
00:04:15,993 --> 00:04:17,027
Hiding something?

87
00:04:18,627 --> 00:04:20,227
No, there's nothing like that.

88
00:04:21,993 --> 00:04:23,581
This is really upsetting.

89
00:04:25,566 --> 00:04:28,301
I told him to go to law school,
but he insisted on philosophy.

90
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,703
So what if he had gone to law school?

91
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:33,876
Eun Hyeong is smart.
He could've passed the bar...

92
00:04:33,876 --> 00:04:37,878
and become a judge, prosecutor, or lawyer.

93
00:04:39,075 --> 00:04:41,148
The bar exam's been gone for years.

94
00:04:41,463 --> 00:04:44,484
These days, even law school graduates...

95
00:04:44,726 --> 00:04:46,793
struggle to find jobs.

96
00:04:46,793 --> 00:04:50,857
How can Eun Hyeong be unemployed?

97
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,627
He applied to other schools,
so let's wait.

98
00:04:53,895 --> 00:04:54,895
He'll get into at least one.

99
00:04:55,627 --> 00:04:56,627
Right?

100
00:04:57,193 --> 00:05:00,000
There's no way
he'll just go down like this.

101
00:05:00,293 --> 00:05:01,993
Let's trust him.

102
00:05:08,460 --> 00:05:09,460
Cho Seong Jun.

103
00:05:10,193 --> 00:05:12,111
The more I think about it,
the more upset I get.

104
00:05:12,627 --> 00:05:15,093
How could you deceive me twice?

105
00:05:20,786 --> 00:05:21,786
"Unemployed"...

106
00:05:22,227 --> 00:05:24,457
means someone who lost their job.

107
00:05:24,457 --> 00:05:26,993
Does that mean you'll be jobless, Dad?

108
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,994
Where did you learn that word?

109
00:05:29,293 --> 00:05:30,327
Dad,

110
00:05:31,527 --> 00:05:33,132
I'm seven.

111
00:05:34,193 --> 00:05:37,170
Bit Na, the way you talk and think...

112
00:05:37,907 --> 00:05:40,627
feels a bit ahead of your age.

113
00:05:40,627 --> 00:05:42,375
I think that's because of me.

114
00:05:42,593 --> 00:05:45,427
Right now,
you shouldn't be worrying about me.

115
00:05:45,794 --> 00:05:48,282
Go talk to Mom already.

116
00:05:49,427 --> 00:05:52,218
All right, that's enough for today.

117
00:05:57,327 --> 00:05:58,393
Good night.

118
00:05:58,393 --> 00:05:59,949
Good night, Dad.

119
00:06:08,293 --> 00:06:09,736
Did it have to be today?

120
00:06:10,627 --> 00:06:12,439
I asked you to wait a little.

121
00:06:12,593 --> 00:06:14,073
I had no choice.

122
00:06:14,407 --> 00:06:16,374
What do you mean, no choice?

123
00:06:17,927 --> 00:06:19,295
If I hadn't done that,

124
00:06:19,627 --> 00:06:21,275
you would've just kept worrying
and never said a word.

125
00:06:22,393 --> 00:06:23,960
To pay for your parents' trip,

126
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,860
you even thought about taking out
our savings.

127
00:06:26,327 --> 00:06:27,960
How did you know that?

128
00:06:31,427 --> 00:06:33,459
You left all the evidence here.

129
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,393
I wasn't really going to take them out.

130
00:06:36,893 --> 00:06:39,666
I just ran the numbers
and thought about it.

131
00:06:40,056 --> 00:06:41,537
Whether you were just thinking or not,

132
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:43,560
did you forget our promise?

133
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,660
We said we'd buy a house...

134
00:06:45,660 --> 00:06:47,907
before Bit Na starts elementary school.

135
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,043
How could you even think...

136
00:06:50,043 --> 00:06:51,845
about taking that money out
to pay for your parents' trip?

137
00:06:51,845 --> 00:06:54,281
I said I was just thinking about it.

138
00:06:57,693 --> 00:06:58,693
But honey,

139
00:06:59,727 --> 00:07:01,443
rather than worrying about the future,

140
00:07:01,443 --> 00:07:03,447
Dad's 60th birthday
is right around the corner...

141
00:07:03,447 --> 00:07:04,447
Are you going to keep this up?

142
00:07:05,427 --> 00:07:06,627
What if Bit Na wakes up?

143
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,214
I have an early flight tomorrow.

144
00:07:11,593 --> 00:07:13,360
Even if I sleep now,
I'll barely get five hours. Move.

145
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,940
Okay, we'll talk later.

146
00:07:24,127 --> 00:07:25,245
Should I turn off the light?

147
00:07:27,527 --> 00:07:28,527
All right then. Sleep.

148
00:07:35,793 --> 00:07:36,927
What's this?

149
00:07:36,927 --> 00:07:40,026
This professional and luxurious look is
so unlike you.

150
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:43,830
Right,
you started at a big company yesterday.

151
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,098
Nice.

152
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:47,593
Dressing appropriately...

153
00:07:47,593 --> 00:07:48,760
is the most basic rule.

154
00:07:49,593 --> 00:07:51,537
Then I'll get going.

155
00:07:51,727 --> 00:07:52,727
Wait.

156
00:07:52,827 --> 00:07:56,136
But this backpack and those sneakers...

157
00:07:57,093 --> 00:07:59,916
don't quite match.

158
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:02,315
So you want me to carry a tiny handbag?

159
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:04,017
You know I carry everything with me.

160
00:08:04,193 --> 00:08:06,185
Anyway, what happened yesterday?

161
00:08:06,488 --> 00:08:08,088
Bit Na said there was no family party.

162
00:08:08,993 --> 00:08:10,260
Something came up.

163
00:08:10,847 --> 00:08:12,192
What did you do this time?

164
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,760
Not me, my brother.

165
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:16,496
Eun Hyeong? What happened?

166
00:08:16,693 --> 00:08:18,260
I'll tell you later. I'm off.

167
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:19,260
Okay.

168
00:08:19,627 --> 00:08:20,834
Cho Eun Ae,

169
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:23,603
don't get intimidated by the big shots.
Let's go!

170
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:26,973
(Kangsu Construction)

171
00:08:45,093 --> 00:08:46,960
Everything looks so different.

172
00:08:48,193 --> 00:08:49,193
Nice.

173
00:09:03,634 --> 00:09:05,334
She's putting on quite a show.

174
00:09:07,793 --> 00:09:08,793
Look at her.

175
00:09:18,860 --> 00:09:20,393
Good morning.

176
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:24,606
Ms. Cho,
are you the same person as yesterday?

177
00:09:24,606 --> 00:09:26,933
You look completely different.

178
00:09:30,036 --> 00:09:32,267
Morning coffee is here.

179
00:09:33,527 --> 00:09:34,647
Manager Victory.

180
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:37,474
I can buy my own coffee.

181
00:09:37,659 --> 00:09:38,926
Sorry? Okay...

182
00:09:40,213 --> 00:09:41,213
Thank you.

183
00:09:42,193 --> 00:09:43,620
- Here.
- Thank you.

184
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:46,960
Want some?

185
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,689
Sorry. Would you like a coffee?

186
00:09:49,893 --> 00:09:51,260
No, thank you.

187
00:09:52,193 --> 00:09:55,860
What time do banks open again?

188
00:09:57,069 --> 00:09:59,399
You can send money anytime these days,
right?

189
00:09:59,913 --> 00:10:02,446
I'll send it.

190
00:10:03,293 --> 00:10:04,403
Good morning.

191
00:10:04,793 --> 00:10:06,405
- Hello.
- Hello, sir.

192
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,748
Team Manager, just a moment.

193
00:10:16,693 --> 00:10:18,084
Don't tell me you're going out again.

194
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:20,060
Yes.

195
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:22,027
What are you doing right now?

196
00:10:22,027 --> 00:10:24,827
Are you just coming in
to clock in at the office?

197
00:10:24,827 --> 00:10:26,292
Yes. Is there a problem?

198
00:10:28,293 --> 00:10:29,293
Seriously.

199
00:10:34,627 --> 00:10:35,627
Team Manager.

200
00:10:37,694 --> 00:10:41,081
May I ask where you go
for fieldwork every day?

201
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:45,445
Why is everyone so interested
in my fieldwork?

202
00:10:46,093 --> 00:10:47,813
Sorry if I'm overstepping,

203
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:51,418
but I was wondering
if you don't intend to compete at all.

204
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:53,880
Seung Ri.

205
00:10:54,406 --> 00:10:55,406
Yes?

206
00:10:57,994 --> 00:11:00,693
- Gyeol.
- Take good care of our new hire.

207
00:11:00,693 --> 00:11:02,043
She's hard to read.

208
00:11:02,527 --> 00:11:04,197
At least during the orientation period...

209
00:11:04,961 --> 00:11:06,166
Don't worry about that.

210
00:11:06,781 --> 00:11:09,214
But are you really not going
to tell me where you're going?

211
00:11:10,938 --> 00:11:12,872
It's a trade secret.
Keep up the good work.

212
00:11:23,393 --> 00:11:24,954
He went out again today.

213
00:11:25,927 --> 00:11:27,627
What do you think he's up to?

214
00:11:27,627 --> 00:11:28,660
How would I know?

215
00:11:29,448 --> 00:11:32,060
Do you think he just accepted the race...

216
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:34,527
because he couldn't say no
to his grandfather?

217
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:35,628
I don't think so.

218
00:11:36,127 --> 00:11:38,860
When he told me he'd changed his mind
and wanted to try competing,

219
00:11:38,860 --> 00:11:40,727
it felt different.

220
00:11:40,969 --> 00:11:42,202
Same with the team setup.

221
00:11:42,503 --> 00:11:43,970
The team? What about it?

222
00:11:44,227 --> 00:11:45,805
He said he wanted to try something new,

223
00:11:45,805 --> 00:11:48,193
different from Kangsu Construction.
Who knows?

224
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:51,978
By the way, did you see
my team's outsourced design proposal?

225
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:54,260
I did, but isn't it a bit too aggressive?

226
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:56,983
I told you we'd bring in
the best design team in the country.

227
00:11:56,983 --> 00:11:58,044
If that backfires...

228
00:11:58,044 --> 00:12:00,119
and raises fairness issues, what then?

229
00:12:00,327 --> 00:12:03,122
Isn't it fair
to provide support according to each plan?

230
00:12:03,693 --> 00:12:05,525
My team's plan isn't just domestic.

231
00:12:05,527 --> 00:12:07,987
It targets the global market.

232
00:12:08,580 --> 00:12:10,236
I'm putting everything on the line
for this race.

233
00:12:11,193 --> 00:12:12,298
I'll trust you, Dad.

234
00:12:14,374 --> 00:12:16,402
Now you're finally fired up.

235
00:12:17,227 --> 00:12:18,293
That's the right attitude.

236
00:12:18,293 --> 00:12:19,739
At today's board meeting,

237
00:12:19,927 --> 00:12:22,841
they'll set
the detailed evaluation schedule...

238
00:12:22,841 --> 00:12:24,227
and outline for the race.

239
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:26,127
Yes, understood.

240
00:12:26,127 --> 00:12:28,120
Right. Wait!

241
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,786
What was her name again? Cho Eun Ae.

242
00:12:31,187 --> 00:12:33,753
She's not going to cause any trouble,
right?

243
00:12:33,867 --> 00:12:36,622
Gyeol said he'd take responsibility
and picked her for his team,

244
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:37,760
so I'm sure he'll handle it.

245
00:12:38,054 --> 00:12:40,655
There's nothing wrong with getting results
without lifting a finger,

246
00:12:40,655 --> 00:12:42,962
but don't push her too hard
or pressure her.

247
00:12:43,764 --> 00:12:45,531
She's the daughter of my closest friend.

248
00:12:45,531 --> 00:12:47,834
Of course, I'll keep that in mind.

249
00:12:48,825 --> 00:12:50,970
All right, get going. You can do it!

250
00:12:51,586 --> 00:12:54,174
Let me see.

251
00:12:55,693 --> 00:12:58,456
The phone is off. After the beep...

252
00:12:58,456 --> 00:13:00,446
What's keeping him so busy?

253
00:13:01,627 --> 00:13:03,749
I asked to meet you
since the president recommended you,

254
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:06,686
but the team members are not comfortable.

255
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:09,660
They're all about your children's age.

256
00:13:12,793 --> 00:13:14,493
Age doesn't matter.

257
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,860
I'll work hard if you give me a chance.

258
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,460
With credentials like yours,

259
00:13:20,460 --> 00:13:23,060
you should be an advisor
or an outside director.

260
00:13:24,327 --> 00:13:25,327
We really can't...

261
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,293
I'm sorry. You even came all this way.

262
00:13:30,547 --> 00:13:31,547
It's fine.

263
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:36,383
Thank you for your time.

264
00:13:38,127 --> 00:13:41,027
Hello? Yeah, it's nothing much.

265
00:13:56,187 --> 00:13:58,171
Is this your way of being professional?

266
00:13:58,533 --> 00:14:01,374
You said you'd be gone for two hours,
so I let it slide,

267
00:14:01,574 --> 00:14:02,974
and you show up after two and a half?

268
00:14:03,627 --> 00:14:05,644
I'm really sorry.

269
00:14:07,927 --> 00:14:10,593
Hey, Seong Jun, perfect timing.

270
00:14:10,593 --> 00:14:12,719
Why weren't you answering your phone?

271
00:14:13,287 --> 00:14:15,221
I had something urgent.

272
00:14:15,393 --> 00:14:17,634
Hello, sir.

273
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,201
Hello.

274
00:14:19,727 --> 00:14:22,628
I told my father about you,
and he was really glad.

275
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,897
He came in today for the board meeting.

276
00:14:24,897 --> 00:14:25,965
Want to come say hello later?

277
00:14:26,393 --> 00:14:28,627
His father... The chairman?

278
00:14:29,627 --> 00:14:31,093
Yeah, okay.

279
00:14:31,727 --> 00:14:34,340
Okay, I'll call you after the meeting.
Keep up the good work.

280
00:14:37,993 --> 00:14:39,312
I didn't know you were...

281
00:14:40,633 --> 00:14:43,650
Please. It won't happen again.

282
00:14:44,012 --> 00:14:45,685
- I'll get back to work now.
- Yes.

283
00:14:49,093 --> 00:14:50,893
The CEO and the chairman are backing him?

284
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:55,993
Even I, Ju Yong Man, am backing him too.

285
00:15:00,527 --> 00:15:03,002
God, Buddha, Allah,

286
00:15:03,525 --> 00:15:05,092
Dragon King, Mountain Spirit,

287
00:15:05,553 --> 00:15:08,611
gather your power, all of it...

288
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:12,343
(The email has been sent.
Your webtoon was successfully delivered.)

289
00:15:16,727 --> 00:15:19,885
I'm going to work out,
so fix your own meal.

290
00:15:20,207 --> 00:15:21,988
- It's in the fridge.
- Got it.

291
00:15:22,493 --> 00:15:24,256
Go ahead.

292
00:15:25,059 --> 00:15:26,359
Did you submit it?

293
00:15:27,012 --> 00:15:30,029
Yeah, just now.
I've got a really good feeling this time.

294
00:15:30,029 --> 00:15:32,096
When haven't you had a good feeling?

295
00:15:33,026 --> 00:15:34,400
If you fail again,

296
00:15:34,827 --> 00:15:38,037
you'll stop chasing that pipe dream,
got it?

297
00:15:39,493 --> 00:15:41,251
Why are you jinxing me?

298
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:43,760
Go on, get out.

299
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:45,560
Where did you put your sister's cardigan
you wore yesterday?

300
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:46,927
I dropped it off at the cleaners'.

301
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,893
Pick it up and put it back in her closet.

302
00:15:49,893 --> 00:15:51,117
Don't fight again.

303
00:16:00,227 --> 00:16:03,540
Is Oh My Oz not online today?

304
00:16:05,299 --> 00:16:06,299
She's here.

305
00:16:07,227 --> 00:16:08,593
Oh My Oz,

306
00:16:08,593 --> 00:16:12,371
I submitted my masterpiece
to the contest today.

307
00:16:13,179 --> 00:16:16,912
Dare I say,
I might finally reveal myself...

308
00:16:17,193 --> 00:16:19,065
to the world soon.

309
00:16:20,127 --> 00:16:21,978
I dare say so too.

310
00:16:23,583 --> 00:16:26,061
By the way,

311
00:16:26,061 --> 00:16:27,927
what's going to happen
with "The ER Witch?"

312
00:16:29,633 --> 00:16:32,591
A week feels like a year waiting for it.

313
00:16:33,927 --> 00:16:35,861
You're a real fan.

314
00:16:36,362 --> 00:16:39,827
Right, I ran into that psycho again.

315
00:16:41,213 --> 00:16:43,330
Something ridiculous happened.

316
00:16:43,999 --> 00:16:44,999
Same here.

317
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:48,607
I ran into that crazy girl again.

318
00:16:49,613 --> 00:16:51,446
Just thinking about it makes me shudder.

319
00:16:52,053 --> 00:16:55,859
But thanks to that,
I started planning my next piece.

320
00:16:56,460 --> 00:16:58,884
A brutal, hardcore revenge story.

321
00:16:59,493 --> 00:17:02,227
You're turning reality into art?

322
00:17:03,027 --> 00:17:04,593
I'm really looking forward to it.

323
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:09,137
So this is what it feels like
to have someone expect something from you.

324
00:17:12,620 --> 00:17:13,653
Figures.

325
00:17:15,493 --> 00:17:16,927
We really click.

326
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:23,600
What's this?

327
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:27,046
It's a gift from the chairman to Madam.

328
00:17:27,446 --> 00:17:28,565
From Father?

329
00:17:29,727 --> 00:17:31,960
Mother, come here.

330
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:34,927
Father sent you a gift.

331
00:17:34,927 --> 00:17:37,359
A gift? What is it?

332
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,019
Open it and see.

333
00:17:54,927 --> 00:17:56,008
Ms. Lee Yeong Hwa,

334
00:17:56,475 --> 00:17:59,045
let's go on a date today.

335
00:17:59,827 --> 00:18:02,160
Make sure you wear this dress.

336
00:18:03,314 --> 00:18:05,111
What is this?

337
00:18:05,527 --> 00:18:06,827
Is it a date invitation?

338
00:18:07,660 --> 00:18:08,821
A date? Please.

339
00:18:10,093 --> 00:18:13,092
Father is so romantic.

340
00:18:13,361 --> 00:18:15,995
Like father, like son.

341
00:18:17,493 --> 00:18:18,864
You should've seen...

342
00:18:19,693 --> 00:18:21,634
the Chairman's tender expression...

343
00:18:22,927 --> 00:18:24,860
when he was choosing this dress, Madam.

344
00:18:24,860 --> 00:18:26,105
That's enough.

345
00:18:27,127 --> 00:18:28,660
Are you heading out?

346
00:18:28,927 --> 00:18:31,760
Yes, I started working out
with Seung Ri's mom.

347
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:34,760
Good, you've made up. Go on.

348
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:36,749
Yes, I'll be back.

349
00:18:39,993 --> 00:18:42,388
Get dressed nicely later.

350
00:18:42,627 --> 00:18:44,957
I'll have the car ready on time.

351
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:54,466
Why does he keep...

352
00:18:57,306 --> 00:18:59,506
All right, let's do it.

353
00:19:00,927 --> 00:19:03,575
If that's what you want.

354
00:19:09,441 --> 00:19:11,617
In dance, position is everything.

355
00:19:11,993 --> 00:19:14,660
Don't forget to secure the front spot.

356
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:18,227
But why here, of all places?

357
00:19:18,693 --> 00:19:21,226
What if we run into Min Ho's dad
or Gwon Sik?

358
00:19:23,527 --> 00:19:25,664
We're part of Kangsu Group.

359
00:19:25,906 --> 00:19:28,673
Why go somewhere else
when our company has such a great program?

360
00:19:28,893 --> 00:19:29,893
Hurry up.

361
00:19:30,593 --> 00:19:31,593
Still...

362
00:19:37,793 --> 00:19:41,347
Let's see... The cultural center is...

363
00:19:55,993 --> 00:19:58,230
I can't let this slide.

364
00:20:15,713 --> 00:20:18,651
Did you move the water bottles
that were here?

365
00:20:19,227 --> 00:20:22,831
Yes. People come before water bottles.

366
00:20:22,831 --> 00:20:25,124
You should take spots in order of arrival.

367
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:27,060
What are you talking about?

368
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:29,793
The bottles were there
because we came first.

369
00:20:29,793 --> 00:20:31,926
Just stand there.
That's the front row too.

370
00:20:33,093 --> 00:20:35,100
I have to be in the center!

371
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:37,067
Move.

372
00:20:37,507 --> 00:20:38,971
Why should I move?

373
00:20:38,971 --> 00:20:40,906
What a strange woman!

374
00:20:41,893 --> 00:20:44,364
This is my spot.

375
00:20:44,364 --> 00:20:46,160
What's wrong with you?

376
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:49,193
Stop it, people are watching.

377
00:20:49,193 --> 00:20:50,411
Enough.

378
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:37,193
Dress codes do matter,

379
00:21:37,193 --> 00:21:38,193
but this isn't it.

380
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:43,135
Who even invented these?

381
00:21:43,627 --> 00:21:45,860
There's a limit to ignoring ergonomics.

382
00:21:49,775 --> 00:21:51,076
Now I can finally breathe.

383
00:21:54,227 --> 00:21:57,416
Hello? I'll be right there.

384
00:22:09,693 --> 00:22:13,160
She's been struggling
with these shoes all day.

385
00:22:21,126 --> 00:22:22,385
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

386
00:22:22,947 --> 00:22:24,293
Yes?

387
00:22:24,293 --> 00:22:25,544
Are you Cinderella?

388
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:27,346
What? Cinderella?

389
00:22:29,727 --> 00:22:31,150
Why do you have these, Team Manager?

390
00:22:31,150 --> 00:22:33,152
Why leave your shoes
lying around anywhere?

391
00:22:34,327 --> 00:22:36,027
My feet hurt so much,

392
00:22:36,027 --> 00:22:38,027
I changed into sneakers and forgot.

393
00:22:38,527 --> 00:22:41,042
If your feet hurt,
you should wear indoor shoes.

394
00:22:42,727 --> 00:22:45,664
Indoor shoes? Thanks for the tip!

395
00:22:47,727 --> 00:22:50,215
- What's going on?
- It's nothing.

396
00:22:50,993 --> 00:22:54,206
But why did the CPO call everyone?

397
00:22:54,993 --> 00:22:56,341
We'll find out inside.

398
00:22:57,140 --> 00:22:58,677
Right.

399
00:23:01,067 --> 00:23:02,960
At today's board meeting,

400
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,393
the competition schedule
for Team One and Team Two was finalized.

401
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:08,787
The first round will be next month.

402
00:23:09,293 --> 00:23:10,556
A competition?

403
00:23:10,556 --> 00:23:12,709
The evaluation will cover each team's...

404
00:23:12,710 --> 00:23:16,060
retirement community theme, concept,
and design proposals.

405
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:19,693
Keep that in mind and prepare accordingly.

406
00:23:20,127 --> 00:23:21,127
- Yes.
- Yes.

407
00:23:21,127 --> 00:23:25,093
Also, to welcome the new members,

408
00:23:25,093 --> 00:23:27,072
I'm thinking of a team dinner
for the whole Strategic Planning Division.

409
00:23:27,727 --> 00:23:29,493
There's a Chinese restaurant nearby
that's really good.

410
00:23:29,493 --> 00:23:31,027
That place is famous.

411
00:23:31,027 --> 00:23:32,027
Sounds good.

412
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:33,778
All right, make a reservation there.

413
00:23:36,027 --> 00:23:39,284
I had no idea there'd be a competition
between the teams.

414
00:23:40,793 --> 00:23:41,793
I should've told you earlier.

415
00:23:42,347 --> 00:23:44,846
We haven't even had a meeting yet.
What do we do?

416
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:48,100
Mr. Han, bring the compiled materials
from this morning.

417
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:49,267
Yes, Manager.

418
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:03,308
Team Manager, I have something to say.

419
00:24:03,760 --> 00:24:05,360
I'm busy. Later.

420
00:24:06,527 --> 00:24:08,060
Is he doing this or not?

421
00:24:11,419 --> 00:24:14,386
I only found out yesterday...

422
00:24:15,627 --> 00:24:17,690
that you work at our company.

423
00:24:18,427 --> 00:24:21,493
I should've come to see you sooner.
My apologies.

424
00:24:21,493 --> 00:24:24,663
It's fine. Life keeps us busy.

425
00:24:26,246 --> 00:24:30,012
We've lived different lives, but I hope...

426
00:24:31,027 --> 00:24:35,507
you can reconnect
and support each other again.

427
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:38,744
Of course.
I'll do my best to make that happen.

428
00:24:42,293 --> 00:24:43,382
I'm sorry.

429
00:24:43,893 --> 00:24:46,973
This old man isn't in the best health.

430
00:24:47,660 --> 00:24:50,089
Are you okay?
Should we go to the hospital right now?

431
00:24:50,089 --> 00:24:52,324
No, don't make a fuss.

432
00:24:52,927 --> 00:24:54,626
- It'll pass soon.
- Chairman.

433
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:56,595
It would be best if you left early today.

434
00:24:56,595 --> 00:24:59,331
No, I have an evening engagement.

435
00:24:59,593 --> 00:25:01,727
You can reschedule it.

436
00:25:01,727 --> 00:25:02,951
It's fine.

437
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:08,273
Look, I'm perfectly fine.

438
00:25:08,482 --> 00:25:10,342
What's his evening engagement?

439
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:17,476
Everyone, please leave. I need to rest.

440
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:21,787
Sorry, it's been a while since we met,
and yet...

441
00:25:22,027 --> 00:25:23,188
Not at all, sir.

442
00:25:25,593 --> 00:25:26,593
Take care of your health.

443
00:25:28,060 --> 00:25:30,429
- I'll step out for a moment.
- Okay.

444
00:25:36,460 --> 00:25:37,793
You overdid it today.

445
00:25:37,793 --> 00:25:39,916
You had a three-hour executive meeting.

446
00:25:40,646 --> 00:25:43,442
I don't know what your evening plan is,

447
00:25:44,377 --> 00:25:45,944
but can't you postpone it?

448
00:25:46,734 --> 00:25:50,616
It's my most important appointment.
I can't postpone it.

449
00:25:51,785 --> 00:25:53,318
What kind of appointment is it?

450
00:25:54,455 --> 00:25:56,321
A date with Ms. Lee Yeong Hwa.

451
00:25:57,732 --> 00:25:58,732
What?

452
00:25:59,340 --> 00:26:00,693
What? Lung cancer?

453
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,160
This is bad.

454
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:05,487
More importantly,
how did your interview go today?

455
00:26:06,147 --> 00:26:07,207
You got it, right?

456
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,360
No, it didn't go well.

457
00:26:10,169 --> 00:26:12,702
The staff seemed burdened...

458
00:26:13,073 --> 00:26:14,139
by my age and experience.

459
00:26:14,608 --> 00:26:16,608
I'm sorry,
after all the trouble you went to for me.

460
00:26:17,127 --> 00:26:18,160
I'm the one who's sorry.

461
00:26:18,599 --> 00:26:20,899
I should've made sure
it was more solid before the interview.

462
00:26:22,727 --> 00:26:23,727
An interview?

463
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:27,519
Mr. Seo, did you send Seong Jun
to another company for an interview?

464
00:26:27,627 --> 00:26:29,721
Yes, sir. What's the problem?

465
00:26:29,927 --> 00:26:31,833
Of course there's a problem.

466
00:26:31,833 --> 00:26:33,425
Why are you sending him elsewhere?

467
00:26:33,573 --> 00:26:35,928
Sending him? Is he some kind of commodity?

468
00:26:36,733 --> 00:26:37,999
Seriously.

469
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:41,293
Why are you being so hard on me?

470
00:26:41,293 --> 00:26:43,702
What is wrong with you two? Stop it.

471
00:26:44,860 --> 00:26:46,171
What if someone sees you?

472
00:26:47,927 --> 00:26:49,908
I heard your father isn't well.

473
00:26:49,908 --> 00:26:51,743
I should've come to see him sooner.

474
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:54,246
It's fine, you came now.

475
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:57,527
I should get going. See you later.

476
00:27:01,093 --> 00:27:03,293
That guy is driving me crazy.

477
00:27:04,027 --> 00:27:05,952
He must really hate you being by my side.

478
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:07,826
What are you talking about?

479
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:10,129
He wouldn't even consider...

480
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:11,929
making a position for you here,

481
00:27:11,929 --> 00:27:14,065
but he'd send you off to interviews
at other companies.

482
00:27:15,093 --> 00:27:17,536
He's clearly trying
to separate you and me.

483
00:27:17,827 --> 00:27:20,852
That's not it. Don't misunderstand.

484
00:27:21,693 --> 00:27:23,475
I still have work to do. I'll get going.

485
00:27:28,693 --> 00:27:29,727
Wait a second.

486
00:27:30,493 --> 00:27:33,993
Having Cho Seong Jun by my side
isn't a bad look.

487
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:36,460
Actually, very good.

488
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:43,995
Since I'm here,
maybe I'll see Eun Ae before I leave.

489
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:46,360
The Strategic Planning Division is...

490
00:27:52,687 --> 00:27:55,320
Excuse me. Can I ask you something?

491
00:28:03,382 --> 00:28:06,385
(Our Happy Days)

492
00:28:06,593 --> 00:28:08,427
Eun Ae, what is this money?

493
00:28:08,427 --> 00:28:10,355
If you live long enough,
you get to see days like this.

494
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:12,263
Your career is anything but ordinary.

495
00:28:12,263 --> 00:28:13,659
- Besides...
- Are you hoping...

496
00:28:13,659 --> 00:28:15,060
I drop out of the competition?

497
00:28:15,260 --> 00:28:16,493
Cut me some slack.

498
00:28:16,493 --> 00:28:18,560
I really want to do well in this race.

499
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:20,332
- He's a team manager.
- Team Manager!

500
00:28:20,332 --> 00:28:22,227
He needs to start something
for me to even try.

501
00:28:22,227 --> 00:28:24,060
No, you can't go today.

502
00:28:24,060 --> 00:28:26,538
Did you accept the intern offer...

503
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:28,340
because you have an ulterior motive?

504
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:30,108
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
